Vertical Navigation
	Home.html
	About.html
	Blog.html
	Contact.html
		<nav class="clearfix">
			<a href="index.html">Home</a>
			<a href="about.html">About</a>
			<a href="blog.html">Blog</a>
			<a href="contact.html">Contact</a>
		</nav>
		a {
			display: block; --> change from inline to block --> break into their own new lines and width assigned to them
			padding: 10px;
			width: 200px;
		}
		a:hover {
		background-color: #f1f1f1;
		}

Floatinga and Clearing
	Div still stacks on top of one another
	Float -- Horizontally or share horizontal space. CSS
		Left, Right, None
		Left: Single Line (similar to inline element)
		Can't assign width or height to inline objects. so we use float.
		1. Create column layout
			The code looks like this:
				 .article {
				 width: 280px;
				 padding: 10px;
				 margin: 0 10px;
				 float: left;
				 }
		2. Text Wraps
		3. Horizontal Navigation
	Clear --
		clear:both --> elements should begin on its own new line
		.clearfix:after{
			visibility: hidden;
			display: block;
		}

Horizontal Navigation
	Home, About, Blog, Contact - xxx.html
	nav {
		background color:
		font-family:
	}
	a {
		background color:
		color:
		text decoration:
		display: block;
		float: left; -- to the left and 1 line
		padding: 20px;
	}
	.clearfix:after {
		visibility: hidden;
		display: block;
		content: " ";
		clear: both;
		height: 0;
		font-size: 0;
	}
	a:hover {
		background-color: #aaaaaa;
	}

